      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, that's much better. it helps them bridge the gap between policy and economic theory. last thing though—to really round out their prep, can you provide a summary of the core philosophical/moral arguments for prioritizing the rights and interests of a nation's own citizens over universalist or humanitarian claims? my students need to be able to defend the idea that a state's primary moral obligation is to its own people without sounding like they're just being dismissive of others.",
